---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Knowledge Base" description="Learn about competitor analysis, tech stacks, and digital marketing strategies.">
  <div class="container pb-24">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1 class="text-gradient page-title">Knowledge Base</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-secondary max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Deep dives into competitor analysis, tech stack research, and modern web architecture.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="articles-grid">
      <article class="glass-panel article-card">
        <div class="article-content">
          <span class="badge mb-4">Competitor Analysis</span>
          <h2 class="article-title">How to Identify a Competitor's Ad Tech Stack</h2>
          <p class="article-excerpt">
            A comprehensive guide to finding out exactly how your competitors are buying, tracking, and converting their traffic using hidden tracking pixels.
          </p>
          <a href="#" class="article-link">Read full post &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="glass-panel article-card">
        <div class="article-content">
          <span class="badge mb-4">Web Development</span>
          <h2 class="article-title">Why Everyone is Moving to Astro and Next.js</h2>
          <p class="article-excerpt">
            We analyzed 10,000 top enterprise marketing sites. The sheer volume of migrations away from traditional monoliths to modern SSR frameworks is staggering.
          </p>
          <a href="#" class="article-link">Read full post &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="glass-panel article-card">
        <div class="article-content">
          <span class="badge mb-4">Case Study</span>
          <h2 class="article-title">Deconstructing the Stripe.com Tech Stack</h2>
          <p class="article-excerpt">
            Stripe's developer experience is legendary. We use SiteIntelica to look under the hood and deconstruct the frontend frameworks powering their gorgeous UI.
          </p>
          <a href="#" class="article-link">Read full post &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
      
      <article class="glass-panel article-card">
        <div class="article-content">
          <span class="badge mb-4">Data Privacy</span>
          <h2 class="article-title">The Rise of Privacy-First Analytics</h2>
          <p class="article-excerpt">
            Our global scan data shows a massive 400% uptick in the adoption of tools like Fathom and Plausible Analytics as companies move away from Google.
          </p>
          <a href="#" class="article-link">Read full post &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .page-header {
      text-align: center;
      padding-top: 6rem;
      padding-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .page-title {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .articles-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(350px, 1fr));
      gap: 2rem;
      max-width: 1000px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .article-card {
      transition: transform var(--transition-smooth), box-shadow var(--transition-smooth);
    }

    .article-card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-5px);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-glow);
    }

    .article-content {
      padding: 2rem;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      height: 100%;
    }

    .article-title {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: hsl(var(--text-primary));
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.3;
    }

    .article-excerpt {
      color: hsl(var(--text-secondary));
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      flex-grow: 1;
    }

    .article-link {
      color: hsl(var(--accent-primary));
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 600;
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      transition: color var(--transition-fast);
      margin-top: auto;
    }

    .article-link:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
      color: hsl(var(--accent-secondary));
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
